This item is of an intricate design, crafted with an eye for detail and a love for art. The efficiency and beauty weaved into this item espouse elven technique. The beautiful craftsmanship of the aquatic variety of the elves are clearly in no way inferior to that of their land-dwelling cousins.

Worn by those who have been personally cursed by a God to eternally walk as a great Death Knight, this plate is now avaible for purchase but only those used to undeath's grip or a dark power can use it.

This plate is embossed with black skulls, sharp ends stained with the blood of old kills. and many who look upon it will know fear.

Legends from the bitter wastelands of the North are exaggerated when shared amidst the meager warmth of a campfire. Rumors of wondrous artifacts, weapons, and armor make their way across the tundra and through the mountains to the ears of adventurers across the world. Sometimes, those rumors are but mere stories. Bardic tales meant to help distract companions from the cold. It is often said that every rumor is rooted in truth, however.

The origin of this axe is not clear. Dwarves, barbaric tribes, and perhaps frost giants alike would undoubtedly boast credit for its creation. Regardless, there is little doubt that such a weapon as this serves as the centerpiece of many stories.

Its edges are jagged and icy, like the maw of some terrible beast of the North whose bite chills to the bone. It almost seems to roar as it cleaves and chews through its victim, leaving in its wake the silence of cold destruction- a void only legends can fill. At times, it can be difficult to know what is truth and what is imagined, but this weapon almost seems eager to be swung...
A mage with quite the selection of wares.
These robes are infused with a darkly, vile magic, and they're splatted with much blood. You absently wonder about their creation.

Many moons ago, the City of Tarkuul existed in a much sinister glory, whence some crusading paladins raized it and naught but the gate bars remained.

You now hold one of these bars, unrusted by time, since Tarkuul's sinister magic has steeped into it's shaft.
A half-orc female that seems to have a task needing done.

Value.value: Uh, hellos! Yous be heres about the recall stones!
Yous have to waits for things, unless you wants to go get the things wes needs.
If yous wants to do that, yous goes to Duergar Blacksmith in forge to get token, then goes to Waafang for fingerwiggler scratchings.
Let mes finish up for yous... *she turns the token over and murmurs in arcane mumblings, making the object shimmer gold for a moment* There yous goes! Take this thens!
Did yous forgets where to goes? Just goes look for Duergar Blacksmith. Then goes finds Waafang. Then come backs and talks to Grimgrod. Then comes sees me.
Hullos, there! Remembers yous can use that token to attune to a Recall Pylon. Wes have one upstairs in our Portal Chamber. Go see Thud outside if yous wants more work. Him's the pretty goblin.
Then yous just comes back and goes see Grimgrod in the other room! She finish up the enchantment. Just brings it back here and I'll activate it for yous!

value.0: Half orc female in her later years.

Value.value: Hullos, dere. Another come with a Recall Stone. Lets me sees it, den. *She chants over the token for several moments, magic leaving her fingertips as she enchants it* Dere yous go. Take this back to Mursha, den.

value.0: A female orc near the jeweler workstation who occasionally works on magic scratchings.

Value.value: Uh, yous have Recall Stone! Lets mes do the scratchings for yous so Grimgrod can finishes. *she takes the piece of metal you received from Duergar Blacksmith and begins to etch on its surface, humming gently to herself* Annnd there yous goes! Here yous goes. You takes to Grimgrod now!

value.0: A large duergar who works the forge.

Value.value: Mursha sent ye for one o' them recall bits, aye? Well, jus' finished one, so take it. *he tosses a small piece of metal to you*

Value.value: One-Eye never sleeps; One-Eye sees all. There is a place for orcs to dwell... here! And here! And here again! There! There is where the orcs shall dwell! And they shall survive, and multiply, and grow stronger. And a day will come when they cover the world, and they shall slay all of your collected peoples! Orcs shall inherit the world you sought to cheat me of!
